        <iri>
          <value>https://cdm.ovh/rsm/topology/topology</value>
          <annotations>
            <annotation>
              <subject>https://cdm.ovh/rsm/topology/topology</subject>
              <property>http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/abstract</property>
              <object>
                <lexicalForm>Full RSM topology; relations between ports are only available as classes (possibly temporal objects) as well as object properties (possibly with temporal annotations, using RDF+).

Syntactic sugar: some properties that are most likely to be used are chained properties, equivalent to derived associations in UML.

Temporality to be expressed using an upper ontology, such as DOLCE+DNS Ultralite.</lexicalForm>
                <datatype/>
                <language>en</language>
              </object>
